form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony, N-4-4-5-A

full_text: Screened by NARA, 9/21/2023 U.S. Department of Justice OMB #1115-0052 Immigration and Naturalization Service Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony Naturalization and Citizenship Branch File or A # ,180 300 NORTH LOS ANGELES STREET A21 235 980 LES ANGELES, CA 90012 Date 5/06/1996 You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony at the DATE, TIME AND PLACE SHOWN BELOW. Date 3/30/1996 MAU NGOC TRAN Time 8:00 AM 3964 CRENSHAW LOS ANGELES CA 90008 Place LOS ANGELES CONVENTION CENTER 1201 SOUTH FIGUERDA STREET LOS ANGELES. CK 90012 You must bring the following with you: This letter, with ALL of the QUESTIONS ON THE REVERSE side answered in ink or on a typewriter. Alien Registration Card. Reentry Permit or Refugee Travel Document. Any immigration documents you may have. If the naturalization application is ON BEHALF OF YOUR CHILD (children), BRING your CHILD (children). If you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, please use the return address in the extreme upper left hand corner of this letter. You will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must appear at an oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process. Form N-445A (Rev. 5/23/94)Y IMPORTANT - PLEASE SEE REVERSE
